{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#11037: hook onMounted has been called when app unmount",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:22:44.183822+00:00",
  "text": "hook onMounted has been called when app unmount\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.4.21\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://github.com/kkagura/test-unmount\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. open /page1 and click the button to go to /page2\r\n2. click button to unmount app\n\n### What is expected?\n\nhook onMounted in Page2.vue should not be called when app unmount\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nhook onMounted has been called when app unmount\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nSystem:\r\n    OS: macOS 12.2.1\r\n    CPU: (8) arm64 Apple M1\r\n    Memory: 73.73 MB / 16.00 GB\r\n    Shell: 5.8 - /bin/zsh\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 16.17.0 - ~/.nvm/versions/node/v16.17.0/bin/node\r\n    Yarn: 1.22.19 - ~/.nvm/versions/node/v16.17.0/bin/yarn\r\n    npm: 8.15.0 - ~/.nvm/versions/node/v16.17.0/bin/npm\r\n    pnpm: 7.11.0 - ~/.nvm/versions/node/v16.17.0/bin/pnpm\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Chrome: 125.0.6422.78\r\n    Safari: 15.3\r\n  npmPackages:\r\n    vue: ^3.4.21 => 3.4.27\n```\n\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
